14 WHEREAS, an overwhelming number of visitors to Georgia report that their reason for
15 visiting was to attend performances, events, exhibits, venues, and arts and culture-related
16 facilities; and
17 WHEREAS, the arts and culture industry serves as a catalyst for generating economic
18 impact, stimulating business development, spurring urban renewal, attracting tourists and
19 area residents to community activities, and improving the overall quality of life in Georgia's
20 cities.
21 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
22 recognize February 2, 2025, as Georgia Arts Day in Georgia and encourage communities
23 throughout the state to celebrate and promote the arts and culture.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
25 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
26 press.
